SBP\ntypes, suggesting that environmental disturbances or satellite accretion in the\nrecent past do not significantly influence the break formation. By dividing our\nsample into early and late morphological types, we find that galaxies with\ndifferent SBP types follow nearly the same tight stellar mass-$R_{25}$\nrelation, which makes the hypothesis that stellar migration alone can transform\nSBP types from TII to TI and then to TIII highly unlikely.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Jun 2020 02:46:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 11 Jul 2020 09:02:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-14"}
