GN broad line region and the IR\nphotometry is consistent with re-radiation by polar dust. Given the fast\nevolution of AT 2017gbl, we deem a tidal disruption event (TDE) of a star a\nmore plausible scenario than a dramatic change in the AGN accretion rate. This\nmakes AT 2017gbl the third TDE candidate to be hosted by a LIRG, in contrast to\nthe so far considered TDE population discovered at optical wavelengths and\nhosted preferably by post-starburst galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Jun 2020 11:00:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Aug 2020 14:35:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-30"}
